						               													<description>Puzzleboard game (for 2 - 6 people)&amp;#10;          (print&amp;amp;play game)&amp;#10;The board game consists of 6*9=54 piece puzzle element and a regular hexagonal dice. The basic board consists of the common play area which is avilable for everyone, and the 6 individual play areas.&amp;#10;At the beginning of the game, the players agree to wich picture (figure) the each want to complete at wich area. In case of debate, the decision will be made by the dice.&amp;#10;After the decision, the puzzle elements have to be placed at the common play area ofthe hexagon, which can happen according to the player's agreement:&amp;#10;- placed according the chosen picture (figure) at the furthest slice from the individual game area,&amp;#10;- the chosen picture at the furthest slice from the individual game area: mixed,&amp;#10;- the puzzle elements are mixed  at the hexagon of the common game area: with the agreement of every player.&amp;#10;Regular movement of the puzzle elements: at the common or individual game area,in patallel with one of the without skipping another element.&amp;#10;After rolling the dice, the number on top of dice will determine the number of steps.&amp;#10;One step is when a player moves a puzzle element to a specific direction: towards the individual game area of the player, without having another puzzle element in the way (without skipinng another element). If there is an element in the way, it should be movedorderly beforhand. If the element not reach individual's game area, it is has to be parked (stored temporarily). In case the puzzle element at the individual game area can only be rotated to the correct position, then it should be moved (orderly) to the O sign first, abd then rotate it here.&amp;#10;The winner is the one who completes the picture (figure) at his own game area.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
